## Diagnosis (from LOCKED facts + trace)

The door lurch is an **asymmetric zoom update**: instant pull-in on ray hit (691/739), then per-frame recovery toward `m_zoom` (602). At door edges the 4-ray diamond flickers hit/miss; each miss lets 602 expand zoom before the next hit snaps it back. At 120 FPS you get **the same per-frame recovery fraction applied 4× more often**, so pop-out is faster in real time and oscillation frequency is higher — exactly matching the observed sharp pop-in/pop-out.

`m_currentZoom` is **not** clamped or reset elsewhere in a way that fights time-scaling — only written at 602, 691, 739, and init (135). Lines 672/743 only **read** it for first-person threshold; `setTarget`/`setFirstPerson` do not touch it.

---

## (i) Time-scale recovery (line 602)

**Current (frame-rate dependent):**

```602:602:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
	m_currentZoom = linearInterpolate (m_currentZoom, m_zoom, ms_cameraZoomSpeed);
```

Default `ms_cameraZoomSpeed = 0.2f` (`ConfigClientGame.cpp:1122`) = 20% of remaining error **per frame**, not per second.

**Adjacent time-scaled precedent (offset):**

```640:640:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
		m_offset = Vector::linearInterpolate(m_offset, m_desiredOffset, elapsedTime);
```

**Same-camera precedent (CockpitCamera — zoom recovery already time-scaled):**

```815:815:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/CockpitCamera.cpp
	m_currentZoom = linearInterpolate (m_currentZoom, m_zoom, std::min(1.0f, elapsedTime * 5.0f));
```

**Exact replacement preserving ~30 FPS feel:**

```cpp
m_currentZoom = linearInterpolate(
    m_currentZoom, m_zoom,
    std::min(1.0f, elapsedTime * ms_cameraZoomSpeed * 30.0f));
```

**Why `* 30.0f`:** at 30 FPS (`elapsedTime ≈ 0.0333`), `t = 0.2` — identical to today. At 120 FPS (`≈ 0.0083`), `t ≈ 0.05` — same **per-second** convergence rate (~6.0/sec effective, matching CockpitCamera's pattern).

**Side effects:** None for wall safety (recovery only expands zoom). Slider semantics become “rate per second calibrated to 30 FPS design point” instead of “fraction per frame”; at 30 FPS behavior is unchanged.

**Must move this block to after collision (see below)** — otherwise 602 expands zoom on the same frame before 739 pulls it back, adding extra wobble even on hit frames.

---

## (ii) Smooth/rate-limit pull-in (691 / 739)

**Current (instant):**

```687:692:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
			if (ClientWorld::collide (getParentCell (), start_w, end_w, CollideParameters::cms_default, result, ClientWorld::CF_allCamera))
			{
				const float lineDistance = start_w.magnitudeBetween (end_w);
				const float t = clamp (0.f, (start_w.magnitudeBetween (result.getPoint ()) / lineDistance) - (0.25f / lineDistance), 1.f);
				m_currentZoom = Vector::linearInterpolate (start_w, end_w, t).magnitudeBetween (start_w);
				m_colliding = true;
```

```738:739:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
				if (hit)
					m_currentZoom = Vector::linearInterpolate (start_w, end_w, minimumT).magnitudeBetween (start_w);
```

Near plane is **0.25 m** (`ConfigClientGame.cpp:972`). Simple path already backs off by 0.25 m (690); default 4-ray path does not.

**Slow pull-in analysis:** if `m_currentZoom > collisionZoom` and you lerp with `t < 1`, the camera stays **farther than the safe distance for that frame** → near plane can show geometry through the wall. Example: need 2 m pull-in, `t = 0.5` → camera sits 1 m inside the safe point for ~8 ms at 120 FPS. **Unacceptable.**

**Safe partial variant** (only if you ever touch pull-in):

```cpp
const float collisionZoom = /* existing computation */;
m_currentZoom = std::min(m_currentZoom, collisionZoom);  // instant when too far — wall-safe
```

That is equivalent to the current assignment when `m_currentZoom ≥ collisionZoom` (the normal door case). A lerp **without** `std::min` clips; a lerp **with** `std::min` is still instant on first contact.

**Side effects of slow pull-in:** visible wall bleed; worse at high FPS + fast turn at door angles. **Do not include in minimal fix.**

---

## (iii) Hysteresis on hit→miss

`m_colliding` is reset every frame at 655 and only reflects **this frame's** hit — no memory across flicker:

```655:655:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
	m_colliding = false;
```

**Minimal hysteresis:** two new members (`m_wallClampZoom`, `m_wallCollisionHoldTimer`), hold last collision distance for ~50 ms after last hit:

```cpp
// anonymous namespace (~line 106)
static const float cs_wallCollisionHoldSeconds = 0.05f;
```

On hit (691/739): compute `collisionZoom`, assign `m_wallClampZoom = collisionZoom`, refresh timer, **`m_currentZoom = std::min(m_currentZoom, collisionZoom)`** (keep instant pull-in).

After collision block, before `move_o`:

```cpp
if (m_wallClampZoom >= 0.f)
{
    m_currentZoom = std::min(m_currentZoom, m_wallClampZoom);
    if (!hit)
    {
        m_wallCollisionHoldTimer -= elapsedTime;
        if (m_wallCollisionHoldTimer <= 0.f)
            m_wallClampZoom = -1.f;
    }
    else
        m_wallCollisionHoldTimer = cs_wallCollisionHoldSeconds;
}

if (m_wallClampZoom < 0.f)
    m_currentZoom = linearInterpolate(m_currentZoom, m_zoom,
        std::min(1.0f, elapsedTime * ms_cameraZoomSpeed * 30.0f));
```

**Side effects:** ~50 ms linger with camera still pulled in after geometry clears (minor “sticky” feel at door); `m_colliding` can stay true during hold (351 offset path) — desirable. Eliminates pop-out on sub-frame ray misses.

---

## Recommended combination

| Fix | Include? | Reason |
|-----|----------|--------|
| (i) Time-scale recovery | **Yes** | Fixes FR-dependent pop-out rate; matches retail ~30 FPS feel |
| (iii) Hysteresis hold | **Yes** | Kills hit/miss flicker — root cause of oscillation at door edges |
| (ii) Slow pull-in | **No** | Cannot be slow without near-plane clip; instant/`std::min` is required |

Also: **delete early line 602**; run recovery only after collision so recovery and hold see the same frame's hit result.

---

## Recommended minimal patch

**`FreeChaseCamera.h`** — add after `m_colliding` (~125):

```cpp
float                  m_wallClampZoom;           // < 0 = inactive
float                  m_wallCollisionHoldTimer;
```

**`FreeChaseCamera.cpp` constructor** (~149):

```cpp
m_wallClampZoom(-1.f),
m_wallCollisionHoldTimer(0.f),
```

