---

## Risk note

| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|------|----------|------------|
| `cs_wallCollisionHoldSeconds` too short | Low | Flicker persists; tune 0.05–0.10 s at cantina door |
| Hold too long | Low | Camera stays pulled in briefly after clearing frame; reduce to ~0.05 s |
| Slow pull-in (if added later) | **High** | Near-plane wall bleed; keep `std::min` instant pull-in |
| `* 30.0f` scale | Low | Correct at 30 FPS; user slider still works, semantics shift to per-second |
| First-person threshold timing | Low | Post-collision recovery preserves existing 672/743 structure |
| Scope | Info | `ShipTurretCamera.cpp:181,195` has the same per-frame pattern — out of scope |

**Verify:** cantina door at 30 / 120 / 144 FPS — sharp-angle approach should lose pop-out; wall-riding in third person should not show near-plane bleed; first-person test should still show no snap (collision block skipped).
